# Context

## Background
This change turns ansorum CLI output into a machine-readable remediation surface for AI coding agents while also packaging the product around an AI reference-layer starter.

## Why This Way
Build, check, audit, eval, and serve now share a structured diagnostics/report envelope so agent loops can fix issues directly from command output. Invalid fixtures and command-level tests were added to keep the error taxonomy stable.

## Gotchas
Example site output under examples/reference-project/public/ is intentionally updated to match the new starter metadata and template rendering.

## Related
- Added --format json/json-stream coverage across commands
- Added --fail-on warn support and warning-promotion behavior
- Added invalid fixture matrix for parser and template failures
